7/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>17</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba:40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Web Application VotoSeguro may be able to impersonate the context of Votante in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Emitir voto</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>E5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T13.1ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd7956e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>16</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba:40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Cross Site Scripting</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>The web server 'Web Application VotoSeguro' could be a subject to a cross-site scripting attack because it does not sanitize untrusted input.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Emitir voto</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T13.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S3ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd7956e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>15</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba:40d59fee-5d6a-4605-b49f-c207431dd795:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Votante External Entity</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Votante may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Web Application VotoSeguro. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the external entity.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Emitir voto</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>ce08f304-2ad7-4f1c-81cb-f57477b482ba</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11