g bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>The web server 'Web Application VotoSeguro' could be a subject to a cross-site scripting attack because it does not sanitize untrusted input.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Obtener Logs</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>efac0430-1398-4b3f-9c67-eca9c1fc2140</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T13.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S3efac0430-1398-4b3f-9c67-eca9c1fc2140b470a2b8-bddd-4f61-8887-87eba698472d6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>b470a2b8-bddd-4f61-8887-87eba698472d</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>12</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>efac0430-1398-4b3f-9c67-eca9c1fc2140:b470a2b8-bddd-4f61-8887-87eba698472d:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Auditor External Entity</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Auditor may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Web Application VotoSeguro. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the external entity.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Obtener Logs</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>efac0430-1398-4b3f-9c67-eca9c1fc2140</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S3d9f212a0-4b16-4542-b5ac-44228617c782524aa728-4d92-4084-9aae-3cec4c83ed976e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>524aa728-4d92-4084-9aae-3cec4c83ed97</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>9</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>d9f212a0-4b16-4542-b5ac-44228617c782:524aa728-4d92-4084-9aae-3cec4c83ed97:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Administrador de Votaciones External Entity</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Administrador de Votaciones may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Web Application VotoSeguro. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the external entity.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>gestión de elecciones</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>d9f212a0-4b16-4542-b5ac-44228617c782</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T13.1d9f212a0-4b16-4542-b5ac-44228617c782524aa728-4d92-4084-9aae-3cec4c83ed976e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>524aa728-4d92-4084-9aae-3cec4c83ed97</b: