actionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Servicio de Correo External Entity</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Servicio de Correo may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to Web Application VotoSeguro. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the external entity.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T13.18f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>121</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Cross Site Scripting</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>The web server 'Web Application VotoSeguro' could be a subject to a cross-site scripting attack because it does not sanitize untrusted input.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T13.1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>E58f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>122</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Using Impersonation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Elevation Of Privilege</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Web Application VotoSeguro may be able to impersonate the context of Servicio de Correo in order to gain additional privilege.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>E5</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>S28f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>126</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing the Web Application VotoSeguro Process</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Web Application VotoSeguro may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to information disclosure by Servicio de Correo. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination process.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>S2</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>T18f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>127</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Lack of Input Validation for Web Application VotoSeguro</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Código OTP may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to a denial of service attack against Web Application VotoSeguro or an elevation of privilege attack against Web Application VotoSeguro or an information disclosure by Web Application VotoSeguro. Failure to verify that input is as expected is a root cause of a very large number of exploitable issues. Consider all paths and the way they handle data. Verify that all input is verified for correctness using an approved list input validation approach.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>T1</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>R68f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>128</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Data Repudiation by Web Application VotoSeguro</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Web Application VotoSeguro claims that it did not receive data from a source outside the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>R6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>I68f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>129</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Data Flow Sniffing</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Information Disclosure</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Data flowing across Código OTP may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>I6</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D38f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>130</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High</b:Priority><b:Properties><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Title</a:Key><a:Value>Potential Process Crash or Stop for Web Application VotoSeguro</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatCategory</a:Key><a:Value>Denial Of Service</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatShortDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>UserThreatDescription</a:Key><a:Value>Web Application VotoSeguro crashes, halts, stops or runs slowly; in all cases violating an availability metric.</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>InteractionString</a:Key><a:Value>Código OTP</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:KeyValueOfstringstring><a:Key>Priority</a:Key><a:Value>High</a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringstring></b:Properties><b:SourceGuid>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a</b:SourceGuid><b:State>AutoGenerated</b:State><b:StateInformation i:nil="true"/><b:TargetGuid>6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:TargetGuid><b:Title i:nil="true"/><b:TypeId>D3</b:TypeId><b:Upgraded>false</b:Upgraded><b:UserThreatCategory i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatDescription i:nil="true"/><b:UserThreatShortDescription i:nil="true"/><b:Wide>false</b:Wide></a:Value></a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:KeyValueOfstringThreatpc_P0_PhOB><a:Key>D48f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041acad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a616e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</a:Key><a:Value xmlns:b="http://schemas.datacontract.org/2004/07/ThreatModeling.KnowledgeBase"><b:ChangedBy i:nil="true"/><b:DrawingSurfaceGuid>0b7d91bc-072f-46ca-b9e4-a0b9384e3a75</b:DrawingSurfaceGuid><b:FlowGuid>cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61</b:FlowGuid><b:Id>131</b:Id><b:InteractionKey>8f993537-6e49-4a9b-aeb2-ad65e925041a:cad1031a-6848-4fad-9d3b-25ba92847a61:6e4d6b69-6023-4d21-abc7-f8d92f11600a</b:InteractionKey><b:InteractionString i:nil="true"/><b:ModifiedAt>0001-01-01T00:00:00</b:ModifiedAt><b:Priority>High<